                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote script="textualisNorthern">Gothic textualis, written by the ‘Trevisa-Gower Scribe’, which Linne R. Mooney attributes to Princeton, Taylor 5; London, University College, frag. Angl. 1 (olim Phillipps 22914); Oxford, Bodleian Library, MS. Bodl. 693; MS. Bodl. 902, fols. 17-184; and Tokyo, Senshu University, MS 1 (olim Schøyen 194). See Linne R. Mooney, ‘The Production of Trinity College, Cambridge MS R.3.2 Revisited’, <title>Journal of the Early Book Society for the Study of Manuscripts and Printing History</title> 24 (2021): 1-25.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="miniature">Fine miniatures, badly rubbed. School of <persName key="person_15318306" role="art">Herman Scherre</persName> (<ref target="https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/000468709">Pächt and Alexander</ref> iii. 814, pl. LXXIX). Scott, <title>Later Gothic Manuscripts</title>, 2:109–110 attributes the miniatures to the Pentecost Master of the Neville Hours. <list>
                        <item><label>(fol. 5r)</label> Nebuchadnezzar and the Man of Metal</item>
                        <item><label>(fol. 10r)</label> Lover and the confessor Genius</item>
                     </list></decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="border">Prologue marked with a four-sided border with floral sprays (fol. 1r). Other books have similar half-borders.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="decInit">Initials in colours with gold leaf.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="flourInit">Pen-flourished initials in blue and red for major text divisions. At first two-line, three-line from fol. 38v.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="rubrication">Rubricated Latin verse headings and running heads, the latter introduced by blue paraphs.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
